BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 2 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
welcomed Monday [2 May] a likely victory of Nelson Mandela's 
African National Congress (ANC) in South Africa's national 
assembly election Sunday. 
  "I evaluate the nation that took apartheid policy is heading 
for democracy," Hata told a reporters at his official residence. 
  Mandela's ANC headed for victory Sunday with a 53 percent 
share of votes, according to reports from Johannesburg. 
  About one-fifth of the votes had been counted out of an 
estimated 23 million ballots cast in South Africa's historic 
all-race elections, it said. 
  The government is expected to issue an official comment on 
the election later in the day, Japanese officials said. 

